<section class="case_studies_content_2columns">
    <div>
        <h2>Validating our solution with users</h2>   
        <p>We asked 11 participants to complete 3 simple tasks on our website based on our main journeys. </p>
    </div> 
    <ul>
        <li>
        <details>
            <summary><h3>Tasks ↗</h3></summary>
            <p>We started by asking our participants if they have ever user FBAULs website and how frequently. Then we asked them to perform 3 simples tasks: “log on to the website”, “find a mentor” and finally “find a job vacancy”.</p>
          </details>
        </li>
        <li>
            <details>
                <summary><h3>Metrics ↗</h3></summary>
                <p>To validate our solution we measured wether users were capable of successfully completing a task, how much time it took them to complete the task and if wether there were any miss clicks/misunderstandings.</p>
             </details>
        </li>
        <li>
            <details>
                <summary><h3>Results ↗</h3></summary>
                <p>We are happy to report that all tasks were completed successfully with 86% of them being direct successes. We assumed that the majority of the miss click rates were a result of limitations within the prototype (such as the inability to input data in a form box).</p>
            </details>
        </li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="case_studies_content_2columns"> 
    <div>
        <h2>Room for Improvement</h2>   
        <p>Here are some opportunities for improvement that we talked about upon a brief self reflection. </p>
    </div>
    <ul>
        <li>
        <details>
            <summary><h3>Meaningfull Tasks ↗</h3></summary>
            <p>Develop the ability to understand if a discovery method is suitable to answer our research questions from the get go. We spent to much time on non-meaningfull tasks.</p>
          </details>
        </li>
        <li>
            <details>
                <summary><h3>Bigger Sample ↗</h3></summary>
                <p>Expand the sample of interview and survey participants, to include all segments identified.</p>
             </details>
        </li>
        <li>
            <details>
                <summary><h3>Go Internacional ↗</h3></summary>
                <p>Expand our benchmarking analysis to include international competitors.</p>
            </details>
        </li>
    </ul>
</section>

